1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:05,925
This diagram uses concentric circles to show the activation order of the four layers.

2
00:00:05,875 --> 00:00:09,187
Chat sits at the innermost circle for planning.

3
00:00:09,187 --> 00:00:11,737
Skill wraps methodology.

4
00:00:11,737 --> 00:00:14,750
MCP connects external tools.

5
00:00:14,750 --> 00:00:19,587
Cowork and Code sit at the outermost layer, handling execution.

6
00:00:19,587 --> 00:00:29,250
Moving from the inside out is called progressive disclosure—you only activate the next layer when you actually need it, which keeps your context window manageable.

